# EFS: The below commands are used to install EFS packages in your Amazon Linux 2 Servers
# ***=== PRE-REQUISITE ===***
# 1. EC2 & EFS have to be in same Security group
# 2. Security group must be enabled with port 'NFS'
# 3. Amazon-efs-utils package to be installed in all servers

#Run below commands in both Linux instances (Under user-data):

#!/bin/bash
sudo su -
yum update -y
yum install amazon-efs-utils -y
mkdir efs #(Copy & paste command from EFS--> Attach --> Using NFS client)
cd efs
touch file1 #(The 'file1' is created in first instance & the same has to be seen in second instance)
